author: @ThanSnow
text:
Can we take a moment to appreciate the powerful message in this MV?

Right from the start, weâ€™re shown a â€œLoveless Societyâ€ registration form with two â€œyesâ€ boxes checked, pointing to a gray, hyper-controlled, and depersonalizing world. Everyoneâ€™s dressed identically and moves in lockstep, as if they have no choice but to follow the script. Then Yujin, already holding one of those dull, uniform books, just tosses it aside, practically saying, â€œEnough of this!â€

Then thereâ€™s Wonyoung with the donkeys in the library (or classroom)â€”absolutely wild. It tears down the whole â€œserious environmentâ€ vibe, suggesting a critique of a space that prides itself on being â€œculturedâ€ but offers little real freedom of thought.

In the penultimate scene, Yujin literally burns the â€˜Loveless Society Registrationâ€™ formâ€”an unmistakable way of rejecting any forced conformity. Sheâ€™s not merely refusing to sign; sheâ€™s obliterating the entire concept of ever belonging to that cold institution.

I absolutely adore the song, the concept, and of course every single member of IVE! â¤â€ğŸ”¥âœ¨
